🩺 Diabetes Prediction API using FastAPI & Machine Learning

This project is a RESTful API built with FastAPI that predicts whether a person is diabetic or not based on medical input features. It uses a Logistic Regression model along with a Standard Scaler for preprocessing.

🚀 Features
🔍 Predicts diabetes based on user input
⚡ Fast and efficient API using FastAPI
🤖 Machine Learning model (Logistic Regression)
📊 Data scaling using StandardScaler
📦 Model and scaler loaded using Joblib
🌐 Ready for deployment (Render compatible)
🧠 Machine Learning Details
Model Used: Logistic Regression
Preprocessing: Standard Scaling
Libraries:
NumPy
Scikit-learn
Joblib
FastAPI
📥 Input Features

The API expects the following input in JSON format:

{
  "Pregnancies": 2,
  "Glucose": 120,
  "BloodPressure": 70,
  "SkinThickness": 20,
  "Insulin": 80,
  "BMI": 28.5,
  "DiabetesPedigreeFunction": 0.5,
  "Age": 30
}
📤 Output Response
{
  "prediction": 1,
  "result": "Diabetic"
}
🛠️ Installation & Setup
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/diabetes-prediction-api.git
cd diabetes-prediction-api
2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
3. Activate environment
# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

# Mac/Linux
source venv/bin/activate
4. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
▶️ Run the Application
uvicorn main:app --reload

📌 API Endpoints
🔹 GET /

Check if API is running

Response:

{
  "message": "Diabetes Prediction API is running!"
}
🔹 POST /predict

Predict diabetes status

Use tools like:

Postman
Thunder Client
FastAPI Docs


